The only thing wrong was too many people there.<//text>

< UserId.>

<user_name>David Engel<//user_name>< Date>
1525802176377< /Date>
<rate>5</rate>< Review>
This is a great outdoor resource for Sonoma County.  The trails are excellent as is the scenery.  There are excellent views and it provides habitat for numerous species.  Unfortunately, there is one trail that has not yet been built.  Apparently a bridge needs to be constructed.  Also, It's unfortunate that we can't  hike here after dark.  During the winter months, it would be great to hike here after work, but it's already dark.  However, those issues do not detract from the fact that this is a beautiful area of Sonoma County where we can get exercise and go to the mountains to get good tidings as John Muir said.</Review>

<username>amy rdh</username><review>Beautiful hiking park. The trails are challenging and breathtaking. I've been hiking here for almost 20 years and never get tired of it. Most of the trails are great for a leisurely hike that will keep your heart rate up. Plenty of benches to rest and we'll marked trails. Bring water and a snack. It's a warm hike on a sunny day. Some of the trails are currently (April 2019) closed due to damage from the 2017 fires and heavy rain that followed. Still possible to get in a 3+/- mile hike. Less than 1/2 mile is stroller friendly in the entire park. If you have a little one, plan on baby wearing and using trekking poles for stability. You won't be disappointed. Bonus of clean bathrooms with running water at the parking lot.
For non-hikers, there is a picnic area and bocce ball court adjacent to the parking lot.</review>< Rate>
5<//Rate>

<user>113083054238884030099</user><user_name>Euronymus Bosch</user_name>< time>
1564812348292<//time>
<Rating>5<//Rating>< Text>
Gorgeous oak woodland with some casual (mostly flat) trails and some steep ones up into the hills.  The picnic area at the base isn't too impressive but the whole park is a great example of the kind of oak habitats in this region as well as a great example as to what happens to such habitats as they recover from large scale fire damage.  There are even a few placards placed along some of the trails describing some of the details of what the fire did and what's happening now.  I thank the park rangers/staff/habitat restoration people for taking the time and effort to do that.  At the time of writing this, there are a couple areas of main trails still blocked for repair, but most of the park is still perfectly accessible.<//Text>

<userid>102972204917385822173</userid>< name>
Majid Azimian< /name>
<time>1550786096678< /time>< rating>
4<//rating>
< Review>
Have reusable plates for food, though none for coffee / tea orders (unless you buy one from them). However, bring your own container and they gladly fill it, giving you a discount to boot.

Labneh toast was nicely toasted and pleasantly presented. Enjoyed the creaminess of the spread and the zatar.

Appreciate the customization options for creaminess and sweetness for each drink on the menu. Don't arrive with the expectation that Philz's "Tantalizing Turkish" coffee offering is authentic or you will likely leave disappointed. It was nice and hot, and came with a bit of fresh mint on top. (If one opts for the highly sweetened option and zero creaminess, this drink might approach a 'real' Turkish coffee more closely, if desired.)

Staff seem caring. The barista who made my drink patiently explained Philz's process, and the staff taking my food order made sure to spell my name correctly unprompted.

Music volume is assertive, so not necessarily a super mellow hangout acoustically speaking. At mid-day, this Philz has a medium to high volume of customers, a bustling atmosphere with lots of people studying, doing laptop work, etc.</Review>

<Time>1565953986978</Time>< Rating>
5</Rating>
<Review>Delicious coffee!!

I finally ventured out to try some of Philz coffee and it did not disappoint! The shop is very spacious with plenty of room for a study break (free WiFi) or just to hang out with friends. They have a nice selection of light, medium, and dark roast coffees to choose from. Since it was a hot day I went with their mint mojito ice coffee ( $5 for a medium). The barista recommend to get it extra creamy and extra sweet so I went with his suggestion.

After you order at the counter you can either wait for your coffee and pay after or pay right away and then pick up your coffee...so that's kind of interesting and a little bit confusing. Once my coffee was ready they shouted out the name of the coffee and not my name...again interesting. The creamy ice mojito was topped with a huge piece of mint which gave the coffee a hint of mint flavor.

The ice coffee was very good. It wasn't too bitter and I didn't have to add more sugar or cream or anything! It was simply perfect! I was really impressed and now I can't wait to try their hot coffee and all their different kinds of flavored roasts!!< /Review><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPoIDtdkYZxIIyYj3plZKKVwPNbqs0kWXRdMyZK=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</pictures>< Response>

<Review>Yay for Philz! Love the coffee. glad there is one in the OC.

Let's take a look.

Pros:
+I'm a big fan of Philz Coffee options ever since I had them in the Bay Area. Lots of choices for all types of coffee lovers that can be sweetened. My favorites include the mint mojito, the rose, the Tesora and the Dancing Water. For a drink, it's not too pricy (like $4-5ish). Also cheers for text receipts!
+I actually like some of the food at Philz and the options. Some food options like quinoa to avocado toasts and protein breakfast bowls. Also, these items aren't too pricy (overall like $3-6ish).
+Service is super friendly here like all other locations. They'll happily explain the drinks; help you with your drinks and are happy to chat.
+The decor is nice with white walls and a modern look. WiFi isn't too bad for the most part and I believe there are some limited outlets (although as you'll see below, this runs into how busy this place gets).

Cons:
-This place definitely gets super busy. Seating is a bit tough although you'll usually find something either indoors or outdoors. Lots of different seat options from sofas to high tops but do expect a very busy atmosphere. This extends to the line as well.
-The busy atmosphere extends to the parking. Can be a bit tough to find parking in the small parking lot they have just as a heads-up.
-Finally, I've had a couple experiences where the server has forgotten a drink which with how busy this place gets, I totally understand. Just don't be surprised by a few hiccups and bumps.< /Review><rating>4< /rating></record>

<user_id>113936150313858418704</user_id>< name>
Shakir Muhammad< /name>
<date>1468588557997< /date><rating>4< /rating>< text>
Food was good. I like spicy food but others in my party did not. So you have to be sure to ask how hot a dish will be. I had a good taste of 6 dishes that were served, all were quite tasty. For kids or the passive ethnic food eater you can't go wrong with the egg-fried rice or even better the crab-fried rice.

The complaints on customer service.. it's not an Olive Garden that brings you breadsticks every 5 minutes or an upscale place that waits on you hand and foot. The services is polite and fulfills requests. No complaints at all. We were a group of 7 adults and 5 kids and we ate 15 minutes after ordering.

I'd go again. 5 star for the food. 3 stars for the setting. Cheers</text>

<Rating>3<//Rating><review>The food is not bad, in fact I really like it. Fairly greasy is par for the course at this price point. What you'd expect from a cheap Thai place.

But the service leaves a lot to be desired. I only order this for takeout and the delivery time is very unpredictable, but usually over an hour. Last time I ordered from here they told me it would be an hour, then I called after an hour and they said 30 more minutes, clearly having completely forgotten about the order.

I also once got a delivery in 30 minutes flat, and as mentioned above the food is fine so that was quite a nice experience.

In summary YMMV, but if you can find another cheap Thai place with good service then give them your business instead, and spread the word. I've got nothing against this place but they could stand to improve their service.< /review><user>100461407362749378549< /user>< Date>

< username>
alfred martinez< /username>
< Date>
1606298946423</Date>
<rating>5<//rating>< Review>
Like their website says, their tamales are "wet" that is because their are hot (temperature). If you let them cool down (lol if you can resist) then they are not as wet and everything stays together when cutting or getting them out of the husk. Remember they are cash only. They do have an atm, but like everything else it will charge you extra to get your money out. So be prepared and bring cash. I bought some (11/24/2020) 2 dozen cheese and 6 beef, total $53.00. They have a special order system for different tastes (ingredients) but I have tried it, but may do so after the holidays. They opened at 6am I was the 3rd person in line, I got there at 5:55 am. Line gathers quickly. So remember...cash and  a list of what you want.< /Review>

<Rate>1< /Rate>< text>
Had my father go grab tamales for Christmas.
The website says $16 for cold tamales. It use to be $13.  Not a big deal.

My father ended up driving 35 to 40 minutes to place the order and then they said the cold tamales were $20. I know times are tough. But that's not the point.

It just needs to be made clear on the website.
And it would be helpful to answer the phone. The voicemail box is full. We both called three different days.

My father ended up paying because we want to support small businesses and because he has been coming to get tamales here, since it was Lolita's.  Needless to say, this is a Go To spot.

Secondly, He realized after be drove home that they overcharged him by 5 dollars.

It was overall a disappointing experience. This place has good tamales but the business to customer communication needs to clear.

FYI, these are good tamales. Just to be clear.

Merry Christmas< /text>

< text>
First time here. I went about 30 minutes before closing and of course the choice was limited. My fault, but I was able to get a dozen and a half of tamales. Dozen green chili with pork, 3 sweet with pineapple and raisin and 3 sweet corn. They gave me the last green chili pork for free, it was the only one left. So I ate that one to try them out and I am very pleased with the taste. Having a family function and I will be taking the tamales. I believe they will go over very well. I am not a fan of sweet tamales so I may not try those but if the are like the green chili with pork I am sure they will be very good. I will be back to try the others. Red with beef, cheese with chili, red pork, and who know's what else. I may add the fifth star after going back to try the others and hopefully find them tasty and a little bit more spicy. Mmmm tamales...and for the record the gentleman who was at the counter was great. Friendly with a smile as I took a minute to figure out what to order or to come back in the morning. Not difficult just indecisive but with his help places my order. I would recommend this place.<//text>

<time>1479178569535</time><rating>5< /rating><review>Great fund raiser!!! Our church has done fund raisers with Sandra's Tamales for the past 3 yrs. In 2014 we ordered 278 dozen. With that many tamales ordered you would think there would be some mistakes...but no, everything was perfect!! We set up the approximate order a month in advance, then four days in advance called and delivered the money to them. Picked the order up at 9:30 in the morning...it took about 30 mins. to load our three vans with the tamales. We charged $5 more than Sandra's Tamales charged us. < Text>
I loved the atmosphere of the place, it was very cute and a lot of greenery. Nice simple date place. The service was great and quick. The Tagliatelle Bolognese was okay. It wasnt amazing where Ill want to go back for that pasta, but Id like to go back and try other foods on their menu. For it being a homemade tagliatelle, it wasnt that good. Maybe it was just a bad batch? My husband got the Frittata Verona. This was very disappointing. My husband is not a chef but makes much better frittatas than this. The egg was overcooked and the vegetables were very bland. It tasted like an omelette with no seasoning.<//Text>

<user_id>117363273412794767828<//user_id>< Name>
Jamie</Name>
<Date>1527553259779< /Date><rating>4</rating>< text>
There were many things I liked about the restaurant. We went there for lunch,  so the setting was more casual than their dinner. I liked the fresh flower and plant surroundings and the patios. In entirety, it felt cozy, alive, and cute.

Their food pricing seemed reasonable at first, but when I got my food I was a little disappointed. The quality could have been better in my opinion, for example, more veggies, herbs, or toppings to upgrade the flavor a little more. I would strongly suggest to use freshly ground black pepper as well because these little things do make huge differences.

The restroom also felt like a storage with dirty rags hanging and napkins all over - clean and dirty, both.

This place has characteristics, but I think it also has room to reach its potentials.< /text>

Ambiance is so important to me. Greenery, gentle sounds of water falling, hand-painted tables, flowers - these things draw me in and make me want to come back and stay as long as I can. <pictures>None< /pictures><name>Travis Garoutte</name>< Text>
I've never personally had the pleasure of visiting this fine establishment, but based on videos I have seen of this restaurant it seems to have a very pleasant atmosphere and extremely nice employees, especially the owner. Of course I haven't got a chance to try it, but the food also looked absolutely delicious. The vast majority of 1 star reviews you will find are just the result of somebody that had a personal vendetta against Cafe Verona. The individual threatened and kicked a very popular streamer out of the restaurant all while claiming to be the owner and part of the "mafia" while standing right in front of the streamers camera. Fans saw this happen live and immediately started bombing reviews and making threatening phone calls to the restaurant in order to defend their leader/retaliate. The real owner quickly took notice of this, found out what had happened, and exchanged apologies with the streamer while explaining what had happened in another video so most of the fans fixed or removed their ratings, but a fair percentage of them either didn't see the follow up video or just didn't bother to correct their mistake. If I ever find myself in LA I will be sure to make Cafe Verona the first place I eat at. They absolutely never deserved any of the negative attention.<//Text>

<text>Supreme service combined with culinary excellence!

The food here is excellent.  I always order the Tagliatelle Bolognese with the arugula salad.  The plates are perfectly proportioned, leaving you satisfied while allowing room to explore a side dish or dessert.  Be sure to try the Prosecco Royale, which is a refreshingly lite beverage made with sparkling wine and wild black currant. A perfect pairing.

Poor service can ruin the experience at any eatery regardless of how good the food is.  The service here at Cafe Verona is incredible.    Completely attentive without excessive contact is hard to find, but this is exactly what you get here.

Great service and food, you can't go wrong visiting Cafe Verona! I will return often!< /text>< response>

<Rate>4<//Rate><Review>First off, the aesthetically pleasing decor places your mind in a tranquil state. Water running over rocks into small ponds, fauna such as ferns, orchids and herbs grow all around this quiet cozy establishment. In the parking lot I found rosemary, by my table were mint which I added to my tea...ohh so delightful.
The food is savory and made fresh.
I had a spinach frittata, it'sserved with a slice of cantaloupe, orange,a herbed sweet potato mash which has a firm Irish or red potatoe cubed mixed in for a textural balance, and biased sliced cucumbers topped with a dill sauce. Veoila! Bon apettit! The passion and love was in every bite of my meal, this is something you cannot pay someone for. Great food.
It is a small cozy cafe with small sections of seating so you are a whisper away from any associate if you require assistance upon the already great service which is provided and yes they have a sense of humor and actually will tell you about the plant life and any other excites they have to offer.</Review><Pics>None<//Pics><Response>None<//Response><gmap_id>0x80c2b8d8f6f1da1f:0x1885ac20e2f31ab1<//gmap_id></record>
